items.body:
Given the 3 following test cases:

test1.css:

``` css
.header {
  text-align: center;
}
```

test2.css

``` css
@media(min-size: 760px) {
  text-align: left;
}

.header {
  text-align: center;
}
```

test3.css

``` css
.header {
  text-align: center;
}

.text {
  font-family: 'Proxima Nova', sans-serif;
}
```

and running the following python script:

``` python
import magic
magic.from_file("test1.css", mime=True)
magic.from_file("test2.css", mime=True)
magic.from_file("test3.css", mime=True)
```

outputs 

```
'text/plain'
'text-plain'
'text/x-asm'
```

All three of these files are very basic examples of a valid css file.
